----- INPUT -----
; Tests JVM spec requirement: interface with abstract but still has mutually exclusive flags
; Expected warning: JVMS-001 (interface with final/super/enum/module)
; This proves:
;   1. Parser correctly identifies interface has abstract flag (no missing abstract warning)
;   2. Parser still detects all mutually exclusive flags (final, super, enum, module)
;   3. Only the mutually exclusive flags warning is generated
;   4. Bytecode is still generated (warning, not error)

.class abstract interface final super enum module EmptyClass
.super java/lang/Object

.class_end
